1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses probabilistic amplitude shaping (PAS) as a means of varying the spectral efficiency of fiber-optic communication systems, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance of fiber-optic communication systems, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of product codes and staircase codes, which are types of error-correcting codes, and also mentions a soft-assisted decoder, which involves algorithmic techniques. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of probabilistic amplitude shaping to improve the throughput of fiber-optic communication systems, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although less likely than the other categories, the paper does mention the use of soft decision decoding, which is a technique used in some network protocols and algorithms.
